'''Elango Nagarajah''', also known as "Thaimann Elango", is a Tamil film actor, director, producer and lyricist in the Tamil film industry. He began his career in his early ages as a producer for the Tamil film [[Anbudan]], starred [[Arun Vijay]], [[Meena (actress)|Meena]], [[Rambha (actress)]] in the main was released in the year 2000.

Then he worked on the most successful Tamil music album நேசிக்கிறேன் as the [[Music director|director]], [[actor]] and [[lyricist]]. He was the main lead for all the six songs in different zonal like Love and Patriotism.

In 2009, he put all his effort for the Canadian Tamil movie என் செல்லமே, again as director and he starred in the main role. He was the lyricist for the two songs in that film also. The songs were composed by Senthuran and were released in May 2007, winning great acclaim in [[Canada]].
He contributed his words for the songs in the Canadian Tamil Movie Mathi, directed by M.Srirangan and for the Tamil album  by M.Vakeesan.

At last he became a hero in the [[Tamil film industry]] with the film ''[[Azhagiya Pandipuram]]''. The film was directed by N. Rayan who was working for many successful Tamil directors. The most famous [[music director]], [[Bharathwaj]] composed five songs for this movie.

== Filmography ==

Cinema is the ultimate pervert art. It doesn't give you what you desire - it tells you how to desire. Elango is having a great passion for the art of cinema since his teenage. He always believes the quote "Always go with your passions, never ask if it's realistic or not". Nothing came easy for him, only his hard work and dedication made him success in his art.

